CBRE as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to present an opportunity to acquire a significant residential apartment block in one of Sydney’s most prestigious suburbs, Double Bay.

25 Guilfoyle Avenue, Double Bay capitalises on the following key attributes:

- Apartment block which comprises:
  - 1x1 bedroom + study apartments
  - 3x2 bedroom apartments
  - 5x2 bedroom + study apartments
- Gross annual passing income of $253,240^
- Located in close proximity to Double Bay’s retail strip, local amenities and transport infrastructure
- Opportunity to own a substantial residential asset in a tightly held suburb
- Estimated market income $293,280^
- Double Bay Wharf (300m^) and Edgecliff train station (550m^) are both closely situated to the subject property
- Strata titled ready for individual sell down

The property will be sold for sale $9.6 million or nearest offer. Expressions of Interest closing on Monday 28 August at 2pm

^Approximate

For further information please contact the exclusive CBRE selling agents listed.

CBER & BadgerFox exclusively offer 27-29 Knox Street, Double Bay by way of Public Auction on Thursday 31 October 20109 at 10:30AM. Described perfectly as a "Trophy Asset", this substantial freehold building is a rare opportunity to acquire one of Double Bay most significant buildings. Situated in one of Double Bay's most renowned streets, this exceptional investment opportunity is located in Sydney's most prestigious harbour side village.

Housing the newly located ANZ bank, 27-29 Knox Street, Double Bay is an exceptional investment opportunity with the benefit of a professional established tenant with future development potential.

Situated between Sportscraft and Double Bay's famous Twenty-One Espresso and directly opposite the Cosmopolitan Centre. The asset is a single tenancy within a recently renovated and state of the art ANZ Bank.

Features of the asset include:
- Blue chip freehold investment property in the heart of the Double Bay village with development potential;
- High ceilings and extensive glass frontage to Knox Street;
- Rear street access to Knox Lane;
- Wide façade with opportunity for branding opportunity and exposure;
- Estimated net income of $199,217* per annum;
- Long term lease in place with an allocated rent review date in mid-2020;
- Total lettable area 230sqm*;
- Land 230sqm*;
- Flexible B2 local centre zoning;
- Potential development upside (STCA);
- FSR of 2.5:1 and 14.7 metre height limit; and
- Rare opportunity to acquire a low maintenance, passive investment located in one of Australia's most notable suburbs.

27-29 Knox Street set to be offered for Sale via Public Auction by Damian Cooley on Thursday, 31 October 2019 at 10:30AM (AEDT) at:

Cooley CBD
Level 5, 1 Margaret Street
Sydney NSW 2000

CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present 491 New South Head Road, Double Bay. Strategically positioned within short distance to the Double Bay Village and Sydney Harbour, the property is DA Approved for the construction of 9 large residential apartments across 5 storeys and sits above basement parking for 7 vehicles. 

491 New South Head Road, Double Bay provides an exceptional opportunity to developers to capitalise on this convenient position and Development Approval which is underpinned by multiple and diverse income streams. 

491 New South Head Road, Double Bay benefits from the following attributes:
-	DA Approved for 9 apartments comprising 4 x 3 bedrooms, 4 x 2 bedrooms and 1 x 1 bedroom plus study along with basement parking for 7 cars.
-	Approved GFA of 845.23sqm*
-	Short walk to Double Bay Town Centre, Woolworths and Redleaf Beach
-	Holding income from multiple tenancies
-	Zoning: R3 Medium Density Residential
-	FSR: 1.3:1
-	Height Limit: 15 metres
-	Opportunity to capitalise on strong demand from investors, downsizers and families

491 New South Head Road, Double Bay will be offered for sale by Expressions of Interest closing Tuesday, 6 April 2021.
